Reasoning: The paper discusses a distributed storage protocol that is fault-tolerant, asynchronous, and efficient. These are all characteristics of distributed computing and distributed systems, which are covered by the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also mentions Byzantine fault-tolerance, which is a topic in computer security and cryptography, covered by the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of erasure coding and metadata storage also suggests a focus on system design and optimization, which falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Overall, the paper's content and focus make it most likely to belong to the cs.Distributed Systems sub-category.
